Retrieves the color map for an image element. The color map contains information about the mapping of colors used in the image. If the element already has a color map, it will be returned. The colorMap does not include all colors in the image, only those that have been mapped.
See "Shade Master" scritp in Script Library for an example of using this function.

type ColorMap = { [color: string]: string; invertInDarkMode?: boolean; }

